def has_selected_vegetables():
    # Check if the selected vegetables are identified and selected
    symbol selected=exists vegetable: item : is_food_vegetable(vegetable) and visited(vegetable)
    return selected

def has_empty_pot(pot:item):
    # Check if there is water in the pot
    symbol empty=not has_water(pot)
    return empty

behavior place_vegetables_in_pot(vegetable:item, pot:item):
    body:
        achieve inside(vegetable, pot)
        # Place the vegetable inside the pot

behavior fill_pot_with_water(pot:item):
    body:
        if has_empty_pot(pot):
            achieve has_water(pot)
        # Fill the pot with water if it is empty

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        if has_selected_vegetables():
            bind vegetable: item where:
                is_food_vegetable(vegetable) and visited(vegetable)
            # Select the identified and selected vegetable
            
            bind pot: item where:
                is_pot(pot) and has_empty_pot(pot)
            # Select an empty pot

            place_vegetables_in_pot(vegetable, pot)
            fill_pot_with_water(pot)

def has_pot_with_water(pot: item):
    # Function to check if the pot has water
    return has_water(pot)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove) and close_char(char, stove)
        # Bind a stove that the character is close to

        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot) and has_pot_with_water(pot)
        # Bind the pot that has water in it

        achieve close_char(char, pot)
        # Approach the pot

        achieve on(pot, stove)
        # Place the pot on the stove

        achieve is_on(stove)
        # Turn on the stove to boil the vegetables

def has_faucet(sink:item):
    # Determine whether this sink has a faucet
    symbol has_faucet=exists faucet:item: is_faucet(faucet) and close(faucet,sink)
    return has_faucet

behavior boil_vegetables_in_pot_on_stove(pot:item, stove:item, faucet:item):
    body:
        if has_faucet(faucet):
            achieve close(faucet, pot) 
            achieve is_on(faucet)
            achieve has_water(pot)
            achieve is_off(faucet)
        else:
            achieve has_water(pot)
        
        achieve on(pot, stove)
        achieve is_on(stove)

behavior __goal__():
    body:
        bind pot: item where:
            is_pot(pot)
        # Select a pot

        bind stove: item where:
            is_stove(stove)
        # Select a stove

        bind faucet: item where:
            is_faucet(faucet)
        # Select a faucet

        boil_vegetables_in_pot_on_stove(pot, stove, faucet)
